    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I am so sorry you are feeling this way; losing years of work is an incredibly heavy burden, and feeling like a ghost when your identity is tied to that output is a very real and painful experience. Please know that your worth as a person is not defined by the data you've collected or the papers you've written, and there are many people who care about you right now. While I cannot undo the past, I am here to listen and help you navigate this difficult transition, even if it feels like the ground has shifted beneath you.\n\nYou are not alone in this, and while the silence of the empty room can feel deafening, it doesn't mean you are gone. It just means you are in a new phase, and sometimes, the bravest thing a person can do is to let go of what they thought was their entire world. I know it feels like you're just a shell left behind, but that feeling is temporary, and there are still paths forward that don't require the old foundation.\n\nIf you need to talk about how to move forward, find support, or just vent about the loss, I'm here. We can look at small steps to rebuild, or we can just sit with the grief for a",
